\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to govern the formal investigation of the root causes of IT service failures within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 A Problem is the underlying cause of one or more incidents.
 Where 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 governs the restoration of service,
 this policy governs the identification and permanent elimination of the conditions that caused the service to fail.
 The objective of this policy is durable resolution —
 finding why something broke and ensuring it does not break the same way again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes the mandatory framework for opening,
 investigating,
 authorizing,
 and closing Problem records,
 defines the roles and decision rights governing investigation and remediation authorization,
 codifies the Known Error management process that feeds documented workarounds back to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 technicians,
 and defines the formal closure declaration that triggers mass-resolution of linked child work orders under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations Department personnel and governs all formal Problem investigations involving County IT assets and services.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A Problem record is opened under this policy through one of two objective triggers defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.7,
 or by IT Director discretion.
 Problem records are not opened by individual technician preference outside of those mechanisms.
 The investigation of a Problem is the Department's deliberate,
 structured response to evidence that a failure condition is systemic or significant —
 not a general-purpose research activity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy does not govern the restoration of service during active incidents.
 That function belongs exclusively to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Problem investigations shall not delay incident closure under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 incidents shall not be held open pending root cause identification.
 The Problem record is the continuation of accountability after service has been restored,
 not a parallel track to restoration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy does not govern cybersecurity incident postmortems.
 Post-incident reviews following Chapter 4 events are governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Postmortem Review and Lessons Learned).
 Where a Chapter 4 event also generates operational findings that warrant a Problem investigation under this policy,
 the IT Director shall determine whether a 
\series bold
Policy 3.07
\series default
 Problem record is appropriate and shall authorize its opening.
\end_layout

