\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Problem Record Intake
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A Problem record shall be opened through one of the following three mechanisms.
 No other mechanism authorizes the creation of a Problem record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Objective Trigger —
 Major Incident
\series default
:
 Every incident classified as Critical severity under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shall generate a formal Problem record upon closure of the originating incident work order,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.7.
 The technician closing the qualifying incident work order shall open the Problem record no later than the close of business on the calendar day the incident work order is resolved.
 The Problem record shall be linked to the originating incident work order via the Related Issues field in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 at the time of creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Objective Trigger —
 Recurring Incident
\series default
:
 Five (5) or more incidents against the same asset or service,
 within the same work order category,
 within any rolling thirty (30) calendar day window,
 shall generate a formal Problem record.
 The technician closing the fifth qualifying incident shall open the Problem record at the time of that closure,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.7.
 The Problem record shall be linked to all qualifying incident work orders via the Related Issues field in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 at the time of creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director Discretion
\series default
:
 The IT Director may authorize the opening of a Problem record for any failure condition that,
 in the IT Director's judgment,
 warrants formal root cause investigation outside the objective triggers above.
 The IT Director's authorization shall be documented in the Problem record at the time of creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon opening,
 all Problem records shall include,
 at minimum:
 the originating trigger or authorization,
 a description of the symptoms and affected asset or service,
 links to all associated incident work orders,
 and the name of the assigned Investigator.
 The Assistant IT Director shall be notified of all Problem record openings no later than the close of business on the day the record is created.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Relationship to Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 Deprecated Asset Trigger
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Recurring Incident spawn trigger above shall not be conflated with the Deprecated Asset labor ceiling trigger defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.5.
 These are related but distinct mechanisms operating on different windows and asking different questions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 trigger uses a ninety (90) calendar day window to ask whether a Deprecated asset is failing with sufficient frequency to warrant accelerated replacement.
 The 
\series bold
Policy 3.07
\series default
 trigger uses a thirty (30) calendar day window to ask whether something is actively wrong with an asset or service right now.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Both triggers may fire simultaneously on the same asset.
 When they do,
 the Problem investigation and the disposition review shall proceed in parallel as complementary obligations.
 The Problem Investigator shall ask why the asset is failing.
 The IT Director disposition review shall ask whether the asset is worth fixing.
 The findings of the Problem investigation shall be made available to the IT Director as an input to the disposition decision,
 but the two processes shall not be merged or held pending the other's conclusion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Investigation Conduct and Priority
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Investigator Authority
\series default
:

\series bold
 
\series default
The assigned Investigator shall be authorized to pursue root cause through any analytical method appropriate to the failure condition.
 This includes,
 without limitation:
 log analysis,
 network trace and routing review,
 configuration comparison,
 vendor documentation review,
 testing in non-production environments,
 and consultation with subject matter experts within or outside the Department.
 The Investigator's analytical authority shall be unrestricted.
 The Investigator's remediation authority shall be strictly limited in accordance with Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Department's operating philosophy on Problem investigation is that curiosity and investigative drive shall not be gatekept by job title.
 Any staff member at any tier may be assigned as Investigator and shall be given the full investigative access necessary to pursue root cause.
 The quality of the investigation is measured by the rigor of the documentation and the validity of the findings,
 not by the seniority of the Investigator.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Investigation Documentation
\series default
:
 The Investigator shall document all investigative steps,
 analytical findings,
 and intermediate conclusions in the Problem record within twenty-four (24) hours of each action taken,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 Section 6.4.
 Documentation shall be specific and sufficient to reconstruct the investigation by a subsequent reviewer who was not present.
 At minimum,
 the Problem record shall contain:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A description of each investigative action taken and the system or data source examined.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The findings or output of each investigative action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Any hypotheses considered and the basis on which they were confirmed or eliminated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The identified root cause,
 stated with sufficient specificity to inform a permanent remediation proposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The proposed remediation,
 including scope,
 affected systems,
 and estimated implementation effort.
\end_layout

